@3002   = ~BERSERKER: This is a warrior who, during combat, can achieve an ecstatic state of mind that will enable him to fight longer, harder, and more savagely than any person has a right to. Berserkers tend to be barbarian-like in nature, but not always. Sometimes it is a conscious choice that a warrior in training makes. Regardless, opponents on the battlefield will be unsettled when they see the savage and inhuman elements of the Berserker's personality. This class is common amongst dwarves, known to them as the Battlerager.

Advantages:
- May use Berserk Rage ability once per day every 4 levels. 

BERSERK: The enraged state lasts for 30 seconds, and gives +4 to constitution and strength; an extra 1/2 attack per round; immunity to all charm, hold, fear, confusion, stun, and sleep spells; a 2 point armor class penalty; and -3 penalty to saves vs breath.

Disadvantages:
- May only achieve Mastery (three sots) with melee weapons.
- May only become proficient (one slot) with ranged weapons and fighting styles.
~
