@3505  = ~Harrier~
@3506  = ~HARRIER: When corruption takes hold in the centers of civilization, good men become outlaws.  While not a true ranger, with the blessing and divine abilities granted by Mielikki, the Harrier uses a ranger's skills in stealth, combat, and guerilla tactics to fight for freedom and justice.  Often decried as lawless by those in power, the common folk tend to view these dashing heroes with admiration and gratitude.
 
Advantages:
- May achieve Mastery (+++) in light swords, axes, dagger, quarterstaff, and bows.
- Begins with proficiency in single-handed weapon, two-weapon, and two-handed weapon styles.
- Once per day (and twice per day after level 6), may set traps as a thief. The chance of success begins at 30% at level 1, and increases 3% for each level gained.

Disadvantages:
- May cast one fewer spell per day of each level available
- Cannot use Charm Animal ability.
~
