@5802   = ~DRUID: The Druid serves the cause of nature and neutrality. Most comfortable in the wilderness, Druids use their special powers to protect it and to preserve balance in the world.

CLASS FEATURES:
- May not wear armor heavier than studded leather, or equip shields larger than bucklers.
- May use and become proficient (+) with the following weapons: dagger, club, flail, spear, quarterstaff, dart, sling, bow.
- May become Proficient (+) in any fighting style.
- May Shapeshift into various animal forms (see below).
- 15th level: Becomes immune to poison.
- 18th level: Gains 10% resistance to cold, fire, electricity, and acid; gains a further 10% resistance at levels 21 and 24.
- Alignment restricted to true neutral.
- Hit Die: d8

Prime Requisites For Dual-Classing: Wisdom, Charisma

SHAPESHIFTING ABILITIES (Forest Druids):
 1st level: wolf
 3rd level: rat
 4th level: dire wolf
 7th level: lion
 11th level: giant cave bear
 High levels: may learn to shapeshift into a powerful Shambling Mound
~
